Example 2: a method that takes an array of strings, and returns a string that is all those strings concatenated together

# Informal Pseudo-Code

Given an array of strings, iterate through the array one by one. 
Create a new string output variable that is empty.
Iterate through each element of the array and append it to the new string output variable. 
Repeat the process until the array is empty.
Remove trailing whitespace in the string output variable.  
Print the string output variable. 


# Formal Pseudo-Code

START

SET string_output = nil

SET iterator = 0

WHILE iterator < size of array
  append element of array at space "iterator" to string_output
  iterator = iterator + 1 

remove whitespace in string_output

PRINT string_output

END
